2.10	Batkhela	Batkhela	Batkhela (Pashto: , Urdu: ) is the main tehsil and capital of Malakand District, Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Pakistan. According to the 1998 census, the population of Batkhela is 38,222, and it is estimated to be 39,703 according to the World Gazetteer. Batkhela is a popular business city in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province. This beautiful valley is covered by tall hills from all sides and there are many fast flowing rivers which are contribution to its wonderful landscape. One water canal that pours into a small dam in Jaban area is main source of electricity production.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/92/Batkhela_main_bazaar.jpg/280px-Batkhela_main_bazaar.jpg
